## Global flags

| Flag | Default | Purpose |
|------|---------|---------|
| `--agent` | off | One-flag agent mode: turns on `--json`, `--compact`, `--no-color`. |
| `--format` | `json` | `json`, `jsonl`, `csv`, `plain`, or `pretty`. |
| `--json` / `--pretty` | `--json` | Emit JSON for agents or rich output for humans. |
| `--no-color` | off | Disable colored output (also sets `NO_COLOR=1`). |
| `--select id,name` | none | Keep only selected top-level JSON fields. |
| `--compact` | off | Keep high-gravity fields for lower-token agent output. |
| `--quiet` | off | Suppress successful output while preserving exit codes. |
| `--dry-run` | off | Show the request without calling the API. |
| `--rate-limit` | `0` | Max requests/sec across this invocation (`0` disables). |
| `--timeout` | client default | Per-request timeout in seconds. |
| `--profile NAME` | none | Load saved flag defaults from `~/.ducktap/{{ spec.name }}/profiles/<name>.json`. |
| `--cache` / `--no-cache` | `--cache` | Mirror GETs into `~/.ducktap/{{ spec.name }}/mirror.sqlite`. |
| `--cache-ttl` | `300` | Mirror TTL in seconds. |
| `--save NAME` | none | Save successful responses into a local queryable collection. |

## Agent mode

Useful defaults for agents:

```bash
{{ cli_bin }} --agent {% for op in operations[:1] %}{% if op.tags %}{{ op.tags[0] | cmd }} {% endif %}{{ op.operation_id | cmd }}{% endfor %}
{{ cli_bin }} --dry-run {% for op in operations[:1] %}{% if op.tags %}{{ op.tags[0] | cmd }} {% endif %}{{ op.operation_id | cmd }}{% endfor %}
{{ cli_bin }} --select id,name,status {% for op in operations[:1] %}{% if op.tags %}{{ op.tags[0] | cmd }} {% endif %}{{ op.operation_id | cmd }}{% endfor %}
```

Two discovery commands let an agent introspect the CLI without parsing
help text:

```bash
{{ cli_bin }} agent-context           # JSON describing every command and group
{{ cli_bin }} which <keyword>         # search by keyword across ids, paths, summaries
```

Saved profiles let an agent persist a flag set:

```bash
{{ cli_bin }} profile save dev --format jsonl --compact --rate-limit 5
{{ cli_bin }} --profile dev <command>
```

## Local Data

Use `--save` to keep successful responses in the local response lake, then query
or search that collection without making another API request:

```bash
{{ cli_bin }} --save prod {% for op in operations[:1] %}{% if op.tags %}{{ op.tags[0] | cmd }} {% endif %}{{ op.operation_id | cmd }}{% endfor %}
{{ cli_bin }} data query "select path, body from records limit 5"
{{ cli_bin }} data search "needle"
```

Exit codes: `0` success, `3` not found, `4` auth, `5` API error, `7` rate limited, `10` local configuration error.

